<h3>Using Onsen UI with Monaca</h3>

<div class="h3-wrapper">
  <p>The benefit of using Monaca with Onsen UI is that you don't need to setup any environment locally, but still can develop for iOS and Android.</p>

  <h4>1. Sign up to Monaca</h4>

  <p>
  <img src="/images/docs/monaca_logo.png">
  <br>
  <a href="http://monaca.mobi" target="_blank">http://monaca.mobi</a>
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  <a class="btn-download" href="http://monaca.mobi" target="_blank">Sign Up for Free</a>
  </p>

  <h4>2. Create a new project by choosing a template using Onsen UI</h4>

  <p><img src="/images/docs/monaca_dashboard.png" width="600"></p>

  <p>After creating the project, open the IDE.</p>

  <h4>3. Install debugger and run the project</h4>

  <p>You can now run the project on the device. Just install Monaca Debugger and it will download the project and start right away.</p>

  <p>
    <img src="/images/docs/debugger_qr.png">
    <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=mobi.monaca.debugger" target="_blank"><img src="/images/docs/google_play_logo.png"></a>
    <a href="http://itunes.apple.com/app/monaca/id550941371" target="_blank"><img src="/images/docs/app_store_logo.png"></a>
  </p>

  <h4>4. Build into Android or iOS native apps</h4>

  <p><img src="/images/docs/monaca_ide.png" width="600"></p>

  <p>Monaca supports Onsen UI app to be published for iOS, Android, and Chrome Apps. You can easily submit your app to App Store and Google Play.</p>
</div>

<h3>Using Onsen UI for Web sites</h3>

<div class="h3-wrapper">
  <p>You can use Onsen UI <a href="http://bower.io">Bower</a> module for quicker setup.</p>

  <pre>
  $ sudo npm install -g bower
  $ bower install onsenui
  </pre>
</div>
